%% Diagram: Promise reaction lifecycle from .then() to handler invocation
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User code
    participant P as Promise (engine)
    participant H as Host (browser/Node)
    participant Q as Host queue (microtask / V8 µtask)
    participant J as Job runner

    U->>P: p.then(handler)
    note over P: HostMakeJobCallback(handler) captures incumbent realm and settings object
    alt p already settled
        P->>H: HostEnqueuePromiseJob(NewPromiseReactionJob)
    else p settles later
        Note over P: Reaction stored on the promise
        U-->>P: resolve(value)
        P->>H: HostEnqueuePromiseJob(NewPromiseReactionJob)
    end
    H->>Q: append job (FIFO per HostEnqueuePromiseJob order)
    note over U,J: Current synchronous Job runs to completion and the execution context stack drains
    J->>Q: drain queue at microtask checkpoint or between callbacks
    Q->>J: pop oldest job
    J->>P: HostCallJobCallback(handler, value)
    P->>U: handler executes inside its captured realm
